verbose_text: The diagnostic reference ranges defining the concentrations of serum 25 (OH) D approved in Central Europe indicate : vitamin D deficiency with 25 (OH) D concentrations < 20 ng/ml, suboptimal vitamin D provision with concentrations 20-30 ng/ml, optimal / adequate vitamin D level 30-50 ng/ml, high concentrations / upper norm 50-100 ng/ml, toxic vitamin D concentrations> 100 ng/ml [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
